Rivers United on Saturday, extended their lead at the top of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL), following a 1-1 draw with champions Akwa United in Uyo. The visitors took the lead in the 17th minute after Matthew Etim diverted Kazie Eyinnaya’s cross into his own net. Rivers United held onto the lead until the end of the first half. However, two minutes after the restart, Adeyeye Adeyemi levelled for Akwa United after he was set up by Etim. Rivers United are now unbeaten in their last 11 NPFL games. Stanley Eguma’s side remain top of the table with 43 points from 20 matches.